column1: Alison Lundergan Grimes, Secretary of State
Are you in favor of amending the Kentucky constitution to state that the citizens of Kentucky have the
personal right to hunt, fish, and harvest wildlife, subject to laws and regulations that promote
conservation and preserve the future of hunting and fishing, and to state that public hunting and fishing
shall be a preferred means of managing and controlling wildlife?
